    "solution": "<img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/SQ6PLd2RkkJfHddRE/mvsvFm6ZLuXL7md1GOg9ejwN0m0O1/3skQFXCf6jMuJ3nPB8A4Gi/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"AIEEE 2003 Mathematics - Permutations and Combinations Question 215 English Explanation 1\">\n<br><br>6 men can sit at the round table = $$\\left( {6 - 1} \\right)! = 5!$$ ways\n<br><br>Now at the round table among 6 men there are 6 empty places and 5 women can sit at those 6 empty positions.<br><br><img class=\"question-image\" src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/wt8ItfkNTuIN6pRPh/xeDfjcRdlQW5nFbaTaqJoHVPNMcW0/4twbHkUf1YXSzn0KJkQMHS/image.png\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"AIEEE 2003 Mathematics - Permutations and Combinations Question 215 English Explanation 2\">\n<br><br>So total no of ways 6 men and 5 women can dine at the round table\n<br><br> = $$5!\\, \\times {}^6{C_5} \\times 5!$$\n<br><br>= $$5!\\, \\times 6 \\times 5!$$\n<br><br>= $$5!\\, \\times 6!$$",
